 Well in light of recent events i'm afraid i'm going to be leaving the guild. Over the past 2 months i have busted my ass getting my vp key and manaburn. The amount of grinding it takes to get the skill is nothing to laugh at. I talked to fornza about this in great detail but I will point a few things out. A) Unless you're ascent callibur you're not killing Hoshkar or Phara dar w/out manaburn. These dragons were meant to be HARD. And as much as i hate to say it not be cheesed killed by a lame new overpowering wiz ability. Phara dar = Vulak of kunark. Ek has been to VP, they couldn't kill phara dar when they tried, they also had no manaburn. B) The only thing i carried out of VP was the thought that hey, phara dar, hoshkar, made possible by me. C) I don't like calling people out, but honestly pantha, did you grind 50 points to get a skill that your guild relys on to kill vp dragons? Do you really think you deserve to wear robe of azure sky with the amount of work you put in compared to myself and fornza? Especially me because i had burn easily 3 weeks before fornza, plus points to spare and maxed spell crits. D) I will be removing my main and twink next time I log on. Thanks for the fun, but I want no part of something where my hard work isn't respected. Lastly, I'm completely willing to help anyone that asks me, I know some feel the way I do about this issue, whether or not they choose to speak out is their decision. If anyone needs help with anything, I'll do my best to drop what I'm doing and come help you, just give me a tell. Again sorry, but Va's leaders need to learn to warrant achievements, and see the people that are really trying hard to make a difference. Best wishes to all - Tempeste <br>
