<br>
Some of us do not have infinite hours to wait for the GM or guides responses. (While they are off hanging with a guild in ToV or talking to someone who is bored...)<br>
<br>
The way I see it you have four outcomes from petition -<br>
1- You have to log off before it is answered. This is what will happen to me most of the time.<br>
2- The person you have the issues with logs off before they respond.<br>
3- They respond, but the person has stopped his actions an hour or so ago and they give you the canned &quot;oh well we cant help&quot; line.<br>
4- They respond, you speak all nice to them, careful not to upset them so they may listen to you, you do not anger them, they come and watch, then give the guy a warning which amounts to nothing since Verant wants the 12.99 in their pocket.<br>
<br>
Petitioning does not work. I believe all of you can probably tell me of a time it did work, but I guarantee you, the times it does not work FAR FAR out-weigh the few successes.<br>
<br>
I do not know a way to fix this problem. I handled it by not playing cuz I get too frustrated with people.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ulorddaeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lorddaeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Dubious </span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#333333>(7/10/02 9:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tempeste</span><hr size=1> thier policy is 1 warning, then ban, just 2 strikes.<br>
